Men try to rob 13-year-old girl
Two young men aged 19 and 23 allegedly tried to rob a 13-year-old girl on Thursday.
According to information from the police, the men approached the 13-year-old, who was with friends on Kolping Street, at around 2.55 pm because they wanted to make a phone call on the girl's mobile phone.
However, the 13-year-old refused the request and went on with her friends.
One of the perpetrators then tried to grab the girl's mobile phone and necklace, but failed.
The duo fled without any loot.
The two young men were later arrested by the police.
The investigation is ongoing.
